    <div class="ws-container">
        <div class="heading-1">PRIVACY&nbsp;POLICY</div>
        <div>
            <h1 class="heading-2">Information we Collect</h1>
            <p>
                We collect both information that you voluntary provide to us, as well as anonymous information

                about your interactions and experiences whenever you access Mathologica.

                Information that you provide: This is information you submit through our website or service that

                consists of your name, email address, and any other personal information that you willingly

                provide. As this information is provided voluntarily, each user has the choice of whether or not to

                disclose such information. Such information is not required to utilize the primary functions of

                Mathologica.

                Information regarding interactions and experiences: This is information that is collected through

                your use and interaction with Mathologica and consists of your data input, time of data input, as

                well as output data. Furthermore, information including your Internet Protocol (IP) address,

                browser type and version, geographical region, referral URLs, and other data automatically

                supplied by common web browsers is collected through the use of Google Analytics. Google

                Analytics utilizes a variety of cookies in order to obtain such information.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div>
            <h1 class="heading-2">Information Collected from Third-Party Sites</h1>
            <p>
                Upon the use of Mathologica with a Third-Party-Site (“TPS”), including but not limited to social

                networking sites such as Facebook or Twitter, we may collect information that is personally

                identifiable from your established profile with the TPS.

                By granting Mathologica access to your TPS profile, you are authorizing Mathologica.com to

                collect, store and use in accordance with this Privacy Policy any and all information that you

                profile’s privacy settings at the TPS dictate.

                As this connection between you and Mathologica requires your consent and authorization

                through the TPS, it is entirely voluntary and thus you have the choice as to whether you wish to

                disclose such information.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div>
            <h1 class="heading-2">How Information is Used</h1>
            <p>
                Collecting information about our users is an important part of maintaining and improving

                Mathologica. We do not sell, rent, or lease your information to any third parties.

            <br />

                The information collected from Mathologica users helps to refine and improve our content and

                service. Information regarding your interactions and experiences is utilized in an effort to

                understand the population that is utilizing the website, and how we might improve our services

                to better the experience. Information collected though Google Analytics is utilized for internal

                reporting, diagnostic and analysis purposes only.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div>
            <h1 class="heading-2">Cookies</h1>
            <p>
                Upon your visit, one or more cookies are sent to your computer in order to identify you with our

                servers. The primary purpose of these cookies to enhance and improve your experience using
                Mathologica by saving preferences and account settings. Most browsers are configured to

                accept these cookies, however you may choose to disable this feature, or be notified when a

                cookie is sent. Note that disabling cookies may have an impact on the full functionality of

                Mathologica. Mathologica sends cookies to do these things:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Record preferences in regards to degrees or radians.</li>
                <li>Record users last input.</li>
                <li>Record account and login settings.</li>
                <li>Collect demographic information through Google Analytics.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
            <h1 class="heading-2">Security</h1>
            <p>
                Mathologica takes measures to ensure the safety and security of our website and services.

                Included in these measures are secure and encrypted connections obtaining a SSL certificate,

                as well as secure and monitored servers.
            </p>
            <p>
                Although security measures are in place to protect your personal information, there is always

                some risk that an unauthorized third party may find a way around our security systems or that

                transmissions of your information over the internet may be intercepted. Your use of the website

                constitutes an acceptance of such risk.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div>
            <h1 class="heading-2">Legal Disclosure</h1>
            <p>
                We will release information, when necessary, in order to comply with lawful court orders, to

                enforce applicable Terms of Service and to protect the rights, property, and safety of

                Mathologica users and others. This pertains to any information associated with your use and

                interaction with Mathologica. This information may be utilized, in accordance with the law, to

                detect, prevent, or otherwise address fraud, and security or technical issues. Finally, this

                information will be disclosed to government authorities and/or third parties in compliance to

                lawful requests, subpoenas, and any other processes that legally require such disclosure.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div>
            <h1 class="heading-2">Changes</h1>
            <p>
                We may update or improve this Privacy Policy periodically in the future. Upon their posting on

                this page, any such updates or improvements will be effective immediately. Please consult this

                page regularly to see any such changes.
            </p>
        </div>

